@Node "Setup" "MUINList.MiamiPanel - Setup"

  @{u}@{b}Setup@{ub}@{uu}


    First of all you must set MUINList.MiamiPanel as default panel:
    Go to "MiamiDX/Gui/Control panel settings.../Panel module"
    and select "MUINList.MiamiPanel".

    An interface will appear in the panel iff it is set to do
    that. In order to make an interface to be in the panel,
    go to "MiamiDx/Interfaces", doubleclick the interface and
    select the checkmark "Control panel".

    Some settings of the panel are available in
    "MiamiDx/GUI/Control panel settings..".
    There you may set:
    o Hotkey
    o Refresh time
    o Show on startup
    o Show transfer rate
    o Show total traffic
    o Show control gadgets
    o Show speed
    o Show online time
    o Show onl/off gadgets

    There are ignored:
    o Font (set it in MUI)
    o Public screen (set it in MUI)

    Other settings you should take care of are the MUI ones:

    o Windows/Fonts/Small for the On/Offline buttons

    o Groups/Frame/Normal for the Miami gadgets group frame
    o Groups/Bacground/Framed for the Miami gadgets group background

    o NListviews/Misc/Misc2/Leading to something like 6 or 8
    o NListviews/ScrollBar/Horiz_Scrollbar to FullAuto
    o NListviews/ScrollBar/Vertical_Scrollbar to FullAuto

    The MUINList.MiamiPanel GUI is described @{"here" Link "GUI"}.

@EndNode

@Node "GUI" "MUINList.MiamiPanel - GUI"

  @{u}@{b}GUI@{ub}@{uu}


    MUINList.MiamiPanel opens a very simple interface,
    whose main elements are:

    o @{"Menus             " Link "Menus"}
    o @{"Interface list    " Link "IFList"}
    o @{"Miami ctrls group " Link "CGroup"}
    o @{"Preferences window" Link "Prefs"}
    o About window

    ------------------------------------------------------
    Note that pressing the Help button in one of the above
    shows this guide.

@EndNode

@Node "Menus" "MUINList.MiamiPanel - Menus"

  @{u}@{b}Menus@{ub}@{uu}


    The MUINList.MiamiPanel menus are:

    o Project

      - About
        Opens the About window

      - About MUI
        Opens the About MUI window

      - Hide
        The action taken depends on your On iconify setting:
        If you choosed Quit, the panel is quit
        If you choosed Iconify, the panel is iconified

      - Quit
        Quit the panel


    o Miami (See @{"Miami ctrls group" Link "CGroup"})

      - Show
        Open Miami GUI

      - Hide
        Iconify Miami GUI

      - Quit
        Quit Miami


    o Preferences

      - Edit
        Opens the Preferences window

      - Save
        Save preferences (including the interfaces list
        width and order and main window position/dimensions)
        to ENVARC:

      - Use
        Save preferences (including the interfaces list width
        and order) to ENV:

      - Restore
        Load the preferences (including the interfaces list
        width and order) from ENV:

      - Last saved
        Load the preferences (including the interfaces list
        width and order) from ENVARC:

      - MUI settings
        Open the MUI settings window

@EndNode

@Node "IFList" "MUINList.MiamiPanel - Interfaces list"

  @{u}@{b}Interfaces list@{ub}@{uu}


    It contains the interfaces datas.

    If you @{"choose" LINK "Setup"} to have the On/Offline gadget
    you will get one button for each interface.
    Pressing the button will put the interface On/Offline.

    The list has also a ContextMenu that may be opened via
    the right mouse button. The menu may be used to put
    an interface On/Offline.

@EndNode

@Node "CGroup" "MUINList.MiamiPanel - Miami ctrls group"

  @{u}@{b}Miami ctrls group@{ub}@{uu}


    If you @{"choose" Link "Setup"} to have the Miami ctrls, you
    get a group made of 3 buttons. They may
    be used to control Miami:

    o Show
      Open Miami GUI

    o Hide
      Iconify Miami GUI

    o Quit
      Quit Miami

@EndNode

@Node "Prefs" "MUINList.MiamiPanel - Preferences window"

  @{u}@{b}Preferences window@{ub}@{uu}


    The Prefereces window lets you edit MUINL.MiamiPanel
    preferences.

      o Interfaces

        - Traffic format
          . Long
            The traffic is shown in bytes
          . Short
            The traffic is shown in Kb/Mb

        - Grouping
          If selected traffic digits are grouped

        - Rate format
          . Long
            The Rate is shown in bytes
          . Short
            The Rate is shown in Kb/Mb

        - Grouping
          If selected rate digits are grouped

        - Short strings
          If selected, short strings are used (for
          On/Offline gadgets and State)

        - Bold title
          If selected the title of the interfaces list
          is rendered bold

        - Double click
          If selected, you may doubleclik on an interface
          to switch its state

      o Miami ctrls

        - Position
          Let you choose where to put the Miami ctrls group

        - Framed
          If selected the Miami ctrls group is framed

        - Virt Frame
          If selected the Miami ctrls group uses the virtual frame
          If not selected the Miami ctrls group uses the group frame

        - Title
          If selected the Miami ctrls group is titled

      o Options

        - On iconify
          This may sound strange, but because of a MiamiPanel
          as no iconified state, you may decide to simply quit
          the panel when iconified, or to really iconify it.
          If iconified with an icon, the panel searches for
          ENVARC:Sys/MiamiPanel.info .

        - BWin
          If selected the panel will use BWin.mcc as window
          class. Note that a BWin.mcc window has a very
          usefull context menu.

      o Save
        Save preferences and exit

      o Use
        Use preferences and exit

      o Apply
        Apply preferences without saving, and exit

      o Test
        Test preferences without exiting

      o Cancel
        Exit without saving

@EndNode

@Node "Bugs" "MUINList.MiamiPanel - Bugs"

  @{u}@{b}Bugs@{ub}@{uu}


    1. No "Suspending" and "Suspended" interfaces states:
       this is a MiamiDx bug.

@EndNode

